<subSubSection pageId="64" pageNumber="65" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="64.[151,1437,401,858]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,437,462]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Notes.</emphasis>
Some taxonomic problems associated with members of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1903" box="[979,1060,438,461]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Nomada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vegana">
<emphasis box="[979,1060,438,461]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">vegana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group were resolved by 
<bibRefCitation author="Droege" box="[151,396,473,498]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Droege" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref86986" refString="Droege, S., Rightmyer, M. G., Sheffield, C. S. &amp; Brady, S. G. (2010) New synonymies in the bee genus Nomada from North America. Zootaxa, 2661, 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="2010">
Droege 
<emphasis box="[245,306,473,498]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">et al.</emphasis>
(2010)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1903" box="[411,599,473,498]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Nomada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vegana">
<emphasis box="[411,599,473,498]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Nomada vegana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not treated in that paper, but 
<bibRefCitation author="Droege" box="[1017,1258,473,498]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Droege" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref86986" refString="Droege, S., Rightmyer, M. G., Sheffield, C. S. &amp; Brady, S. G. (2010) New synonymies in the bee genus Nomada from North America. Zootaxa, 2661, 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="2010">
Droege 
<emphasis box="[1111,1172,473,498]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">et al.</emphasis>
(2010)
</bibRefCitation>
provide useful information for comparison to other members of the group that occur in 
<collectingRegion box="[988,1099,509,534]" country="United States of America" name="Michigan" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Michigan</collectingRegion>
, including 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1854" box="[1227,1342,509,534]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Nomada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fervida">
<emphasis box="[1227,1246,510,533]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1262,1342,509,534]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">fervida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(and its midwestern dark color form 
<taxonomicName authority="Graenicher" authorityName="Graenicher" authorityYear="1911" box="[486,825,545,570]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Nomada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wisconsinensis">
<emphasis box="[486,505,546,569]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[522,688,546,569]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">wisconsinensis</emphasis>
Graenicher
</taxonomicName>
, previously considered as a distinct species, e.g., by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wolf &amp; Ascher" box="[151,391,581,606]" firstAuthor="Wolf" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="129 - 168" refId="ref106106" refString="Wolf, A. T. &amp; Ascher, J. S. (2009) Bees of Wisconsin (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila). The Great Lakes Entomologist, 41, 129 - 168." type="journal article" year="2009">Wolf &amp; Ascher, 2009</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName box="[452,600,582,606]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Nomada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tiftonensis">
<emphasis box="[452,471,582,605]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[485,600,582,606]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">tiftonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(treated as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Cresson" authorityName="Cresson" authorityYear="1878" box="[961,1230,581,606]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Nomada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heiligbrodtii">
<emphasis box="[961,980,582,605]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[994,1133,581,606]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">heiligbrodtii</emphasis>
Cresson
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mitchell" box="[1271,1436,581,606]" firstAuthor="Mitchell" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="1 - 557" refId="ref96606" refString="Mitchell, T. B. (1962) Bees of the Eastern United States: volume II. N. C. Agricultural Experimental Station Technical Bulletin, 152, 1 - 557." type="book chapter" year="1962">Mitchell, 1962</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Hurd" box="[202,337,617,642]" firstAuthor="Hurd" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="1741 - 2209" refId="ref90811" refString="Hurd, P. D. (1979) Superfamily Apoidea. In: Krombein, K. V., Hurd Jr., P. D., Smith, D. R. &amp; Burks, B. D. (Eds.), Catalog of Hymenoptera in America North of Mexico. Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington, D. C., pp. 1741 - 2209." type="book chapter" year="1979">Hurd, 1979</bibRefCitation>
, and also considered as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Cresson" authorityName="Cresson (Pengelly" authorityYear="1955" box="[876,1088,618,642]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Nomada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="texana">
<emphasis box="[876,895,618,641]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[912,987,618,641]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">texana</emphasis>
Cresson
</taxonomicName>
in earlier drafts of 
<bibRefCitation author="Ascher &amp; Pickering" firstAuthor="Ascher" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="47" refId="ref82570" refString="Ascher, J. S. &amp; Pickering, J. (2017) Discover Life bee species guide and world checklist (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila). Draft- 47. Available from: http: // www. discoverlife. org / mp / 20 q? guide = Apoidea _ species (Accessed 7 August 2017)" type="book chapter" year="2017">Ascher &amp; Pickering, 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
